<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ911127-0032</DOCNO><DOCID>911127-0032.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- OIS Optical Imaging Systems Inc.:   Guardian Industries Corp.   Takes a 28% Stake in Firm</HL><DATE>11/27/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION</SO><CO>   OVONC WNEWS</CO><MS>TECHNOLOGY (TEC)</MS><IN>BUYBACKS, REDEMPTIONS, SWAP OFFERS (BBK)INDUSTRIAL TECHNOLOGY andamp; PRODUCTION, QUALITY CONTROL (ITC)TENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM)</IN><NS>BUYBACKS, REDEMPTIONS, REPURCHASES, SWAPS (BBK)PERSONNEL ANNOUNCEMENTS, PROMOTIONS, APPOINTMENTS (PER)ACQUISITIONS andamp; MERGERS, TAKEOVERS, BOARD BATTLES (TNM)</NS><RE>MICHIGAN (MI)NORTH AMERICA (NME)NEW YORK (NY)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   OIS Optical Imaging Systems Inc. said it completed astock-purchase agreement with Guardian Industries Corp.,Northville, Mich.   Under the agreement, Guardian invested $10.5 million inreturn for a 28% stake in OIS Optical. Guardian also has anoption, exercisable at any time within three years, to investan additional $10.5 million in return for a 51% equityownership. Guardian manufactures glass products.</LP><TEXT>   In connection with Guardian's investment, William Manning,OIS Optical's largest shareholder, converted his outstandingpreferred stock, warrants and certain convertible notes ofOIS Optical into common. Mr. Manning also has agreed toconvert the remainder of his convertible notes to stock ifGuardian exercises its option.   Immediately after shareholder approval of the investment,Rex Tapp, Guardian's director of technical development, waselected chairman of OIS Optical's board.   OIS Optical, Troy, Mich., develops electronic displays andelectronic imaging and scanning systems.</TEXT></DOC>